docs.abstract: What were once believed to be exotic technologies are now being considered to fill in perceived safety gaps.
docs.snippet: What were once believed to be exotic technologies are now being considered to fill in perceived safety gaps.
docs.lead_paragraph: In a year when the autonomous vehicle business has hit a big reset button, consensus is growing among designers that self-driving cars just aren’t perceptive enough to make them sufficiently safe. So now engineers are considering using more sophisticated sensors and technology — tech that can see through rain and even look underground.

headline.main: These High-Tech Sensors May Be the Key to Autonomous Cars
headline.print_headline: Autonomous Cars Are Still Learning to See
